Name: HGNC gene name
Description: The HUGO Gene Nomenclature Committee (HGNC) assigns unique symbols and names to human genes.

Name: Ensembl transcript identifier
Description: Each transcript ID includes a unique, stable 11 digit number. Transcripts beginning with ENST are human transcripts (for example, ENST00000369985).

Name: UniProt identifier
Description: UniProt is a high quality, comprehensive protein resource in which the core activity is the expert review and annotation of proteins

Name: Chromosome
Description: Chromosomal location of the DNA variant

Name: Variant classification
Description: Variant classification according to VKGL labs using 5 tier system (B, LB, VUS, LP, P)

Name: Protein chaperoned
Description: Does the protein have interactions with known chaperones?

Name: Total energy
Description: The overall protein stability, integrating all individual energetic contributions.

Name: Backbone H-bond
Description: The energetic contribution from hydrogen bonds formed between backbone atoms.

Name: Sidechain H-bond
Description: The hydrogen bonds involving sidechain-sidechain and sidechain-backbone interactions.

Name: Van der Waals
Description: The stabilizing contribution from van der Waals interactions between non-bonded atoms.

Name: Electrostatics
Description: The effects of electrostatic attractions and repulsions among charged groups.

Name: Solvation polar
Description: The penalty incurred when polar groups become buried and lose favorable interactions with the solvent.

Name: Solvation hydrophobic
Description: The energetic gain from burying hydrophobic groups away from the solvent.

Name: Van der Waals clashes
Description: The energy penalty due to inter-residue van der Waals collisions or overlaps.

Name: Entropy sidechain
Description: The entropy cost associated with restricting the conformational freedom of side chains.

Name: Entropy mainchain
Description: The entropy penalty for fixing the main chain conformation.

Name: Cis bond
Description: The energetic cost of adopting a cis conformation in a peptide bond.

Name: Torsional clash
Description: The intra-residue van der Waals clashes arising from unfavorable torsion angles.

Name: Backbone clash
Description: The backbone-backbone van der Waals overlaps, which are typically excluded from the total energy.

Name: Helix dipole
Description: The electrostatic contribution of the helix macrodipole to the proteinâ€™s energy.

Name: Disulfide
Description: The energetic contribution of disulfide bond formation between cysteine residues.

Name: Ionisation energy
Description: The contribution from ionization events, affecting charged residues or groups.

Name: Aliphatic index
Description: The aliphatic index of a protein is defined by Ikai (1980) as the relative volume occupied by aliphatic side chains (Alanine, Valine, Isoleucine, and Leucine). It may be regarded as a positive factor for the increase of thermostability of globular proteins.

Name: Boman index
Description: The potential protein interaction index proposed by Boman (2003) based in the amino acid sequence of a protein. The index is equal to the sum of the solubility values for all residues in a sequence, it might give an overall estimate of the potential of a peptide to bind to membranes or other proteins as receptors, to normalize it is divided by the number of residues. A protein have high binding potential if the index value is higher than 2.48.

Name: Charge
Description: The net charge of a protein sequence based on the Henderson-Hasselbalch equation described by Moore, D. S. (1985). The net charge is calculated at pH 7 using the Lehninger pKa scale

Name: Hydrophobic moment
Description: The amphipathic character of a peptide or protein region by summing the vector contribution of sidechain hydrophobicities.

Name: Hydrophobicity
Description: The relative affinity of a side chain or molecule for non-polar (hydrophobic) versus polar (aqueous) environments.

Name: Instability
Description: This function calculates the instability index proposed by Guruprasad (1990). This index predicts the stability of a protein based on its amino acid composition, a protein whose instability index is smaller than 40 is predicted as stable, a value above 40 predicts that the protein may be unstable.

Name: Molecular weight
Description: The molecular weight of a protein sequence, calculated as the sum of the mass of each amino acid, expressed in Daltons (Da).

Name: Mass over charge
Description: The monoisotopic mass over charge ratio (m/z) for peptides, as measured in mass spectrometry.

Name: Isoelectric point
Description: The pH at which the protein carries no net electrical charge.

Name: DNA binding site (prob)
Description: Per residue probability sum of DNA binding site

Name: DNA binding site (bool)
Description: Per residue binary prediction sum of DNA binding site
